    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-07T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-07T07:00:00-05:00" n="661"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/8–744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kelley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-07T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 7, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1439. For Pehle WRB from Hirschmann. Ankara No. 120. In a conference today with
                    Mikhailov, First Secretary of the Russian Embassy in Ankara, I expressed the
                    hope that his Government would make special efforts to distinguish between the
                    victims of fascism and the Fascists themselves when the Red Army enters enemy
                    territory. Mikhailov assured me on behalf of the Soviet Government that all
                    citizens in enemy territory would be treated alike as this was a fundamental
                    principle of the Soviet regime and that the victims and those who were
                    incarcerated would be treated with special solicitude. [Hirschmann.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kelley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
